    "course_title": "INTRODUCTION TO LANDSCAPE ARCHITECTURE DESIGN STUDIO",
    "description": "Introduction to the techniques and processes used in solving three-dimensional design problems in the urban and natural environment through studio exercises. Understand how design process and design principles create physical and sensory experiences in our everyday lives. Develop fundamental verbal and graphic communication skills used in the professional design world. Gives attention to the basics of design theory and philosophy.",
